com.camerontec.util.logger

Class AbstractProgressReporter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.logger.AbstractProgressReporter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProgressReporter
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultJournalingPersistentStoreProgressReporter

    public abstract class AbstractProgressReporter
extends Object
implements ProgressReporter
    ProgressReporter implementation that provides progress common reporting functionality.

    This reporter does not output anything - that's up to the implementer.

    Instances of this class are not thread-safe.

      • shouldReport

        protected boolean shouldReport(long chunkCompleted,
                               long cumulativeProgress)
        Returns whether the current progress should be reported.

        This is called for each invocation of onProgress(long) and should therefore return as quickly as possible.

        Parameters:
        chunkCompleted - incremental amount completed
        cumulativeProgress - cumulative amount completed

        whether the current progress should be reported
